race.comment: SUNSHINEINMYPOCKET (5) was an excellent return at Moonee Valley over 1200m, charging home to just miss. This track and trip will suit better, he'll just need a touch of luck from the inside gate. NDOLA (3) returned with a solid win in Adelaide over 1250m and should only be fitter for it. Second up last time in he charged home for second to Sepals at G3 level which reads very well for this. KEEP YOUR COOL (2) is off a let-up but continues to race consistently and maps for every chance. She'll land in the first few, if not in front, and take a bit of beating from there. SO RISQUE (9) has been solid in two runs back from a spell and should be ready to peak now third up. The King Zephyr form is strong for this.
